powershell
# Assume $resultjson contains the JSON response from the ACI API
foreach( $tenant in $resultjson.imdata )
{
 $tenantName = $tenant.fvTenant.attributes.name
 Write-Host $tenantName
}
This code snippet does the following:

It uses a foreach loop to iterate through each tenant in the imdata array.

For each tenant, it extracts the tenant's name from the fvTenant.attributes.name property.

It then prints the tenant's name using Write-Host.

*Registering Name Server Proxies*
You can register the name server proxy.

SUMMARY STEPS
configure terminal
fcns proxy-port wwn-id vsan vsan-id

Selected Answer: D
About Registering Name Server Proxies

All name server registration requests come from the same port whose parameter is registered or changed. If it does not, then the request is rejected.

This authorization enables WWNs to register specific parameters for another node.

https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/switches/datacenter/nexus9000/sw/93x/san_switching/configuration/guide/b-cisco-nexus-9000-nx-os-san-switching-configuration-guide-933/n9000_managing_flogi_name_server_fdmi_and_rscn_databases.html

Selected Answer: B
The command fcns proxy-port 21:00:00:b2:c5:71:32:a9 vsan 100 is used in the context of Fibre Channel Name Server (FCNS) configurations on Cisco switches. This command is specifically used to add an entry for a proxy port in the name server database.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

B. It adds an entry for the name server database.

choices.C: It implements a mapping between the WWN and the VSAN.
choices.B: It adds an entry for the name server database.
choices.D: It enables the registration of parameters for another node.

Here's a breakdown of what these commands do:


copy sftp://admin@192.168.10.100/backup.cfg bootflash:///backup.cfg vrf management: This command copies the backup configuration file from the SFTP server to the switch's bootflash storage.
configure replace bootflash:///backup.cfg: This command replaces the current running configuration with the configuration from the backup file stored in the bootflash.

Selected Answer: C
Vrf should be management, however C is the correct answer.
